      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-29T03:23:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can you elaborate more on the reasoning? With the same convention, shouldn\u0027t we also move the build metrics to the rpc module where the build events occur?",
      "parentUuid": "8a085504_3174e18a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "5969568fcb997d323ad8562db1398cb358d989fc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b03688e_1cdc2884",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/internal/metrics/sequence.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-29T04:56:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in general, this approach doesn\u0027t scale well with the number of metrics, and will accumulate ad-hoc metrics that are used in a single place (e.g. sequence). In general, I have the same concern with \"model\" package which keeps all kinds of entities.\n\nSuppose I create a new package with a very specific purpose, and I need a metric. For consistency, I have to create a metric in metrics package, make it public (available to all other packages) and import it. There are at least two weirdnesses:\n1) I have to import metrics package, in order to import something that is very specific to my package. Why isn\u0027t it in my package to begin with? It is kind of private actually.\n2) If I am a third unrelated package and I look at \"metrics\" package, I see a conglomeration of symbols that do not have much to do with each other. In particular.",
      "parentUuid": "dec252cd_946a6fac",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "5969568fcb997d323ad8562db1398cb358d989fc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "252d8994_19ec238c",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/internal/metrics/sequence.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-29T16:59:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, those perfectly make sense. I will write a separate CL to move all them under appengine/rpc.\n\nI\u0027d like to keep the sequence number generation metric because it\u0027s just a copy of the python metric definition without business logic, and we will likely have to use the same metric def for backward-compatibility.\n\nI will move those under appengine/rpc, and rename all metric objects to be private vars.",
      "parentUuid": "9b03688e_1cdc2884",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 1,
